channel.title: World News, News of World, Top World News, World Breaking Headlines - Times of India
channel.description: TOI delivers the Top Latest World news and Headlines from US, UK, Gulf, Pakistan, China, Europe and rest of the world.

image.title: World News, News of World, Top World News, World Breaking Headlines - Times of India

item.title: Attack closes airport in Libyan capital
item.description: Libyan officials say they stopped planes from landing and taking off at Tripoli’s international airport after two explosive projectiles struck a runway.

item.title: France offers 4 warplanes for Baltic air patrols
item.description: France is offering to send warplanes to help provide air patrols over the Baltic states and Poland, officials said Friday, amid growing tensions between the West and Russia and despite a looming big-ticket military deal between Paris and Moscow.

item.title: Nato, Ukraine join military exercise in Bulgaria
item.description: Ukraine has joined two weeks of multinational military exercises that involve troops from 12 NATO member and partner nations, and demonstrate that cooperation continues between the alliance and the crisis-torn former Soviet republic.

item.title: Wave of attacks across Iraq kills 28 people
item.description: A series of attacks north and west of Baghdad today, including two suicide bombings, killed at least 28 people, mainly members of security forces, and wounded dozens, Iraqi officials said.

item.title: Wave of attacks across Iraq kills 25 people
item.description: A series of attacks north and west of Baghdad on Friday, including two suicide bombings, killed at least 25 people and wounded dozens, Iraqi officials said.

item.title: US eyes military supplies for Ukraine
item.description: Kiev has asked for military support from the United States, which US officials, speaking on condition of anonymity, say includes small arms, as well as non-lethal assistance, such as medical supplies.

item.title: Hillary Clinton creates distance from Obama
item.description: As secretary of state, Clinton was a key player in a US effort to reset relations with Russia, a policy that critics say now appears to be a glaring failure.

item.title: Michelle Obama tours Beijing’s Forbidden City
item.description: The two women’s husbands, Barack Obama and Xi Jinping, are expected to meet next week on the sidelines of a nuclear security summit in the Netherlands.

item.title: Thai court voids Feb election
item.description: The February 2 polls, called by Yingluck Shinawatra in an unsuccessful attempt to ease a months-old political crisis, have not yet been completed because of disruption by demonstrators.

item.title: Syrians, Russians, Afghans lead asylum list: UN
item.description: Russia become the second-biggest source of asylum seekers with 39,779, up from 22,650 in 2012.

item.title: No imminent nuclear tests in North Korea: Report
item.description: North Korea, last week, threatened to demonstrate its nuclear deterrence in a move that analysts say could indicate the regime is preparing to carry out a fourth atomic test amid long-stalled disarmament talks.

item.title: Furious Sarkozy lashes out at corruption allegations
item.description: Former French president Nicolas Sarkozy broke his silence on Thursday over corruption allegations threatening his chances of a political comeback, comparing his country to a dictatorship as he angrily fought back against a phone-tap scandal.

item.title: Uruguay to take Guantanamo detainees
item.description: Uruguay's President Jose Mujica said on Thursday that his country had agreed to receive detainees from the US military prison at Guantanamo Bay, calling the decision a matter of human rights.

item.title: Smog insurance introduced in China
item.description: A Chinese insurer is offering smog insurance to travelers visiting six heavily-polluted cities in China during extremely hazy days.

item.title: Xi calls good relations with India his ‘historic mission’
item.description: Chinese president Xi Jinping on Thursday said he regarded improving India-China relations as his “historic mission”. He described himself an “advocate of furthering the India-China strategic partnership”.

item.title: Russia won't attack east Ukraine: US
item.description: Russian defence minister Sergei Shoigu promised his US counterpart Chuck Hagel in a telephone call on Thursday that Moscow would not assault eastern Ukraine.

item.title: Michelle Obama in China on hotly anticipated trip
item.description: Michelle Obama arrived in Beijing on Thursday evening, beginning a hotly anticipated week-long trip during which she will promote education and cultural ties.

item.title: Train crashes into minibus in Turkey, 10 dead
item.description: A commuter train smashed into a minibus on a railway track in southern Turkey on Thursday, killing 10 people and injuring several others.

item.title: 'Nearly half of Syrian chemical weapons removed'
item.description: Nearly half of Syria's declared chemical weapons have been shipped out of the country after two more cargoes were loaded onto vessels in the Mediterranean over the last week.

item.title: EU mulls further sanctions on Russia
item.description: Russia faces further sanctions from the European Union on Thursday over its annexation of the Crimean Peninsula.

item.title: Pakistan government to hold direct talks with Taliban
item.description: The Pakistan government has finalized direct talks with the Tehreek-i-Taliban Pakistan (TTP) and the venue will be decided in the next 48 hours, interior Minister Chaudhry Nisar Ali Khan said Thursday morning.

item.title: Suicide attack in Baghdad cafe kills 46
item.description: A suicide bomber struck inside a Baghdad cafe overnight where customers were watching a football game on TV, killing at least 46 people, Iraqi officials said Thursday.

item.title: Suicide attack in Baghdad cafe kills 12 people
item.description: A suicide bomber struck inside a Baghdad cafe overnight where customers were watching a football game on TV, killing at least 12 people and wounding 38, Iraqi officials said Thursday.

item.title: Afghanistan: 18 killed in Taliban attack
item.description: At least eighteen people were killed on Thursday morning in a Taliban coordinated car bombing and shooting attack on a police station in Afghanistan's Jalalabad city, an official said.

item.title: Afghanistan: Six killed in Taliban attack
item.description: At least six people were killed and 20 injured on Thursday morning in a Taliban coordinated car bombing and shooting attack on a police station in Afghanistan's Jalalabad city, an official said.
